				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">True, but the 3D leap was still important because it allowed for a behind-the-character viewpoint. Behind-the-character allows for far longer distances than a side or overhead view. Otherwise, when a character is moving rapidly across the landscape, the player can't react in time to obstacles or items that just scrolled into view. This let games get away from a &quot;world map&quot;, &quot;town map&quot;, and &quot;indoor map&quot; at three separate scales in favor of one seamless map, leading to the whole sandbox genre.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

